    "John Trapp": "Because she judged him, &amp;c. ] At first she laughed, through unbelief, at the unlikelihood; but afterward she bethought herself, and believed. This latter is recorded, the former pardoned. So #Ge 18:12 , \"Sarah `[char_Sarah_Ref]` laughed within herself, saying, After I have waxen old shall I have pleasure, my lord being old also?\" Here was never a good word but one, viz. that she called her husband lord, and this is recorded to her eternal commendation, #1Pe 3:6 . Isaac then was not a child of nature, but of the mere promise; so are all our graces. We bring forth good things, as Sarah `[char_Sarah_Ref]`\u2019s dead womb brought forth a child.\nVer.\n11. Because she judged him, &c.] At first she laughed, through unbelief, at the unlikelihood; but afterward she bethought herself, and believed. This latter is recorded, the former pardoned. [v_Gen_18_12] So #Ge 18:12, \"Sarah `[char_Sarah_Ref]` laughed within herself, saying, After I have waxen old shall I have pleasure, my lord being old also?\" Here was never a good word but one, viz. that she called her husband lord, and this is recorded to her eternal commendation, #1Pe 3:"
